---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon — Sam Stringer-Hye" description="How this site was built.">
  <section class="colophon-page" aria-label="Colophon">
    <div class="colophon-header">
      <p class="typo-ui-caps" data-reveal style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">About this site</p>
      <h1 class="typo-display-md" data-reveal>Colophon</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="colophon-body">
      <h2 class="typo-headline-lg" data-reveal>Tech Stack</h2>
      <p data-reveal>
        Built with <strong>Astro</strong> for static-first delivery with selective React hydration for interactive components.
        Animations powered by <strong>GSAP</strong> (ScrollTrigger, SplitText).
        Smooth scrolling via <strong>Lenis</strong>. Deployed on <strong>Cloudflare Workers</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="typo-headline-lg" data-reveal>Typography</h2>
      <p data-reveal>
        <strong>Playfair Display</strong> is used for display and headline roles, paired with
        <strong>DM Sans</strong> for body text, titles, labels, and UI elements.
        The serif/sans pairing creates a two-register type system: editorial for impact, geometric sans for readability.
        The 5×3 typescale grid (display, headline, title, body, label × lg/md/sm) follows M3 conventions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="typo-headline-lg" data-reveal>Design Language</h2>
      <p data-reveal>
        The prismatic/CMY (cyan, magenta, yellow) chromatic separation is used throughout as a unifying visual language.
        It appears in scroll reveals, hover effects, the hero animation's temporal RGB split, and the carousel's velocity-driven shadows.
        This references how white light splits through a prism. It's a metaphor for breaking a design system into its constituent parts.
      </p>

      <h2 class="typo-headline-lg" data-reveal>Accessibility</h2>
      <p data-reveal>
        This site respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>: all animations are disabled or minimized when the user has requested reduced motion.
        Navigation is fully keyboard-accessible with focus trapping on mobile, and all images include alt text.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .colophon-page {
    grid-column: 4 / 10;
    padding-block: var(--space-6);
  }

  @media (--2x) {
    .colophon-page {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
      padding-inline: var(--page-margin);
    }
  }

  .colophon-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .colophon-header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
  }

  .colophon-body h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .colophon-body h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .colophon-body p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .colophon-body strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .colophon-body code {
    background: var(--prose-code-bg);
    padding: var(--prose-code-padding-block) var(--prose-code-padding-inline);
    border-radius: var(--prose-code-border-radius);
  }
</style>
